This paper is likely to belong to the Information Theory (cs.IT) sub-category as it deals with decoding algorithms for polar codes, which are a type of error-correcting code used in information theory. It could also belong to the sub-categories of Coding Theory (cs.CC) and Signal Processing (cs.SI) as these fields are closely related to information theory. Additionally, since the paper discusses the complexity of the decoding algorithm, it could also belong to the sub-categories of Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) and Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS).
